{% extends "layouts/base.njk" %}
{% block content %}
  <div class="nhsuk-grid-row">
    <div class="nhsuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
      <h1 class="nhsuk-heading-l">Accessibility</h1>
      <p class="nhsuk-body">
        This prototype is built with the NHS design system, which is designed to meet
        <strong>WCAG 2.2 AA</strong>. Pages are server-rendered and usable without JavaScript;
        the acute crisis view works with JavaScript turned off.
      </p>
      <p class="nhsuk-body">
        We aim for semantic headings, visible focus, sufficient colour contrast, labelled form
        fields and an error-summary pattern on forms. As a prototype, it has not yet had a full
        independent audit or screen-reader pass — that would form part of the production build.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
{% endblock %}
